Rating: 3
I didn't do the creme fraiche-crab thing; instead I made these fritters to accompany Baked Shrimp in Chipotle Sauce, also from epicurious. 1/8 tsp salt sounded bland to me, so I used half a teaspoon instead; I also used scallions instead of red onion for ease of chopping, and skipped the red pepper. With the shrimp and a celery root/jicama/pear remoulade on a bed of baby Red Oak lettuce, this was one of the best dinners I've ever made. Highly recommend.

Rating: 3
This recipe is delicious! Corny corn corn corrrnz in my doo doo. I omitted the red bell pepper, and used seeded Anaheim chilies. I used a total of 3/8 of a tsp of salt instead of 1/8. Also, I added 1/8 tsp of Cayenne Pepper. It was soooo good. Also, it is totally worth it to make home made creme fraiche. Essentially 1T of buttermilk (which you'll have around anyways for the fritters) to every 1C of Heavy whipping cream. Super num numz. I made 1/2 of my fritter batch with crab fraiche and 1/2 without. I felt both were delicious.

