This is delicious and easy to make. I tried the batter before frying and it needed a little bit of salt and pepper. It was so good I ate the leftovers for breakfast the next morning. I am making it again tonight!

Rating: 4
I totally agree with the person who said the fritters were bland, so I added another 1/4 teaspoon of kosher salt (3/8 teaspoon total) and that perked the flavor right up. They were easy to make in quantity, easy to re-heat and a huge hit at every party I've brought them to. Other modifications: I never have buttermilk on hand, so I used 1/4 cup milk and 1/4 cup sour cream instead of the 1/2 cup buttermilk. Instead of using the sour cream with the crab (and I almost never have creme fraiche on hand) I used about 4 tablespoons of heavy cream with a tablespoon of red wine vinegar. And to the people who write the recipes at Gourmet: Instead of telling me how many people it will serve, for these kinds of individual hors d'oeuvres, can you just tell us about how many pieces a recipe makes? I got about 2 dozen pieces.

